\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. C. cvijicii} Kosanin, {\i Glas Srpske Kralj. Akad.}{\b  119}: 23 (1926). Corm-tunic finely fibrous, reticulate. Leaves 2-4, 1·5-3 mm wide, present at anthesis. Flowers solitary, pale cream to deep orange-yellow; throat pubescent. Prophyll absent. Bract and bracteole present, well-exserted from the cataphylls and more or less equalling the perianth-tube. Perianth-tube 1·5-3·5 cm, whitish or rarely purple; segments 1·5-4 × 0·6-0·9 cm, oblanceolate, obtuse. Anthers orange-yellow. Style orange, about equalling the stamens, obscurely divided into 3 expanded stigmatic branches. Capsule 1-1·5 cm, ellipsoid; seeds subglobose, with a distinct strophiole, reddish-brown. Flowering from April to June. 2n = 18. {\i Snow-patches,} 1800-2300 {\i m. • Mountains of Macedonia and E. Albania.} Al Gr Ju.
