\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. C. pelistericus} Pulevic, {\i Glasn. Rep. Zavoda Zast Vt. Prir. }({\i Titograd}) {\b 9}: 39 (1976). Like {\b 19} but leaves 3-5, 1-2 mm wide; flowers 1(-2) deep violet; throat glabrous or minutely papillose; style whitish, exceeding the stamens, shortly divided into 3 whitish shallowly lobed branches. Capsule and seeds unknown. Flowering from May to June.{\i  Snow-patches and damp mountain meadows,} 1900-2300 {\i m. S. Jugoslavia} ({\i Jakupica and Baba Pl}.). Ju.
