\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 23-25}). {\i C. biflorus} group. Corm-tunic smooth, papery to coriaceous, splitting into smooth or dentate rings at the base. Leaves 3-5(-6), 0·5-2·5 mm wide, present at anthesis. Flowers 1-3. Prophyll absent. Bract and bracteole membranous, white, well-exserted from the cataphylls, the bracteole much narrower than the bract. Perianth-tube 2-8 cm, white, lilac, yellow or bronze; segments 1·5-4·5 × 0·4-1·8 cm, oblanceolate or obovate, subacute to rounded. Style yellow to orange-red, divided into 3 slender or expanded branches. Capsule 1-1·5 cm, ellipsoid; seeds brown or reddish, subglobose; strophiole distinct, expanded, flattened at one end. Flowering from October to May.
