\pard\f0\fs28   Plants with yellow flowers, flushed and striped with purple externally, have been recorded from S.C. Jugoslavia (near Nis). These are thought to be hybrids between {\b 23} and {\b 24}, and have been named {\b C}. ×{\b  hybridus} Petrovic, {\i Fl. Agr. Nyss.} 821 (1882).
