\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. C. biflorus} Miller, {\i Gard. Dict.} ed. 8, no. 4 (1768) ({\i C. adami }Gay, {\i C. tauricus} (Trautv.) Puring). Flowers white or lilac-blue, often strongly striped and veined, or strongly tinged with deep purple-blue or brownish-purple; throat white, lilac or yellow. Anthers yellow, sometimes with blackish basal lobes or a greyish connective. Flowering from January to April. 2n = 8, 12, 16.{\i  S. Europe, from Sicilia eastwards.} Bu It Gr Ju Rs (W, K) Si Tu.
